  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT86-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">āṟṟāḷ eṉak kavaṉṟa tōḻikkuk kiḻattic colliyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Uttered by HER to the confidante who was anxious she wouldn't have the strength.</p>
          </div>



        <div xml:id="KT86">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                ciṟaipaṉi yuṭainta cēyari maḻaikkaṭ</l>
<l>                poṟaiyaru nōyoṭu pulampalaik kalaṅkip</l>
<l>                piṟaruṅ kēṭkuna ruḷarko luṟaiciṟan</l>
<l>                tūtai tūṟṟuṅ kūtir yāmat</l>
<l>                tāṉuḷam pulamputo ṟuḷampu</l>
<l>                nānavil koṭumaṇi nalkūr kuralē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <l>Are there other listeners,</l>
                <l rend="indent">stirred up, struck by loneliness, with pain difficult to bear,</l>
                <l rend="indent">with red-streaked rain eyes, the long-checked dew broken out,</l>
                <l>
                    <choice>
                        <seg>to the curved</seg>
                        <seg>of the cruel</seg>
                    </choice>
                    bell's poor voice<note place="foot">Another possibility is to read <term xml:lang="ta">kural</term> not as an object to <term xml:lang="ta">kēṭkunar</term>, but to take the last three lines as a postpositioned exclamation: "[Oh], the voice of the bell ...!".</note> in which the tongue is sounding,
                </l>
                <l rend="indent">
                    <choice>
                        <seg>stirring each time a fly buzzes around the cow,<note place="foot">An alternative to the syntax of the last two lines by Srin.: "the tender sound of the cruel bell which sounds if the tongue [of the bell] moves, every time (-<term xml:lang="ta">toṟu</term>) a fly buzzes (around a) cow".</note></seg>
                        <seg>as the cow with every buzzing stirs up the fly<note place="foot">The cow stirs up the fly, that is, it moves its head to get rid of the fly and thus makes the bell move.</note></seg>
                    </choice>
                </l>
                <l rend="indent">at midnight in the cold season,</l>
                <l rend="indent3">when the rain-laden cold wind spreads?</l>

            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
